\section{LINEX Models}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

The LINEX model has the form

\begin{equation} \label{eq:LINEX_model}
  y = \mathrm{e}^{\left[a_0 \left(2 - \frac{l + e}{k} \right) + a_0 c_t \left(\frac{l}{e} - 1 \right)\right]} \: e ,
\end{equation}

\noindent where $e$ is one of $q$, $x$, or $u$; $a_0$ and $c_t$ are fitting parameters; and $\mathrm{e}$ is the base of the natural logarithm.

